title: 1994–95 Combined Counties Football League
text:
The 1994–95 Combined Counties Football League season was the 17th in the history of the <a href="Combined%20Counties%20Football%20League">Combined Counties Football League</a>, a <a href="association%20football">football</a> competition in England.
The league was won by <a href="Ashford%20Town%20%28Middlesex%29%20F.C.">Ashford Town (Middlesex)</a> for the first time.
League table.
The league was reduced from 21 clubs to 18 after Ditton, <a href="Farleigh%20Rovers%20F.C.">Farleigh Rovers</a> and <a href="Virginia%20Water%20F.C.">Virginia Water</a> joined the <a href="Surrey%20County%20Senior%20League">Surrey County Premier League</a>, and <a href="Frimley%20Green%20F.C.">Frimley Green</a> joined the <a href="Surrey%20County%20Intermediate%20League%20%28Western%29">Surrey Intermediate League</a>.
